	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 11th 9:37 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The karanas are a druid's paradise if you can get a port to Surefalls. Start with bats in QHills if you are under 5 or 6 then head to WK. You can fear kite bears, wolves, and lions till about 9 or 10. At this point you can go fight pincers at the zone entrance to NK. Pincer beetles are awesome to fight with low risk since you can kite them even without sow. Just watch for highland lions and griffs.<br><br>At 12-14 you can start to fight highland lions and borer beetles. Depending on your equipment and skill at 14-16 you can go to EK and fear kite gorge hounds or got to SK and fight elephant calves.<br><br>Needless to say the loot is rather poor but you can get some HQ and MQ cat pelts which are worth a plat or two as well as lion skins from lions. If you get lucky you can get some HQ bear skins from the grizzlies or brown bears which can go for about 20-30pp to players.<br><br>With your animal lines and the large open spaces the karnas are hard to beat for young druids to learn their craft.<br><br>Happy hunting.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
