	   <tr><td colspan=2>Four is the limit that your AOE spell will hit. Even then, they have to be VERY closely packed (think almost visually identical, occupying the same space). Add to that the chance of resists, adds and so forth. . . well, you can see why quad-kiting isn't for the faint of heart. At level 35, those druids you see are just starting out on quad-kiting. They get better with practice!<br>&nbsp;<br>-- Ancarett, who lives at <a href="http://ancarett.com" target=_new>http://ancarett.com</a></td></tr>
