	   <tr><td colspan=2>Alteration, in my opinion, is the way to go. It saves you on ports, healing, and buffs -- the meat of a druid's career. However, if you're a nuking druid or a kiter, evocation or conjuration may be for you. I let Tunare and Fate decide, and just put one point in each and cast as I normally did. As I guessed, Alteration bubbled to the top and hit 50 before the others did. But, don't worry if you regret your choice later on -- there is an easy quest that will reset your specializations and allow you to choose again:<br><br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=711" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=711</a><br><br>Happy hunting!<br>&nbsp;<br>-- <br>[Druid] Lambeau Farstrider (Human)<br>[Rogue] Gripp Tinkersnout (Gnome)<br>&lt;Tragic Heroes&gt; -- Saryrn</td></tr>
